        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer872656239" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18336377689744168200">When a book can take you back a few years with the innocence of its characters; the way they think, the way they talk, it&apos;s pure magic. Everwud made me smile right away with the introduction of Joey. What I loved about him is that in spite of being an orphan he&apos;s full of love and expectation. He&apos;s bright, cheery and all boy. The author put Joey in some situations where it would&apos;ve been easier for him to run for cover than to follow his heart. This story reveals Ms. Dieckmann&apos;s keen imagination a</span>
  <span id="freeText18336377689744168200" style="display:none">When a book can take you back a few years with the innocence of its characters; the way they think, the way they talk, it's pure magic. Everwud made me smile right away with the introduction of Joey. What I loved about him is that in spite of being an orphan he's full of love and expectation. He's bright, cheery and all boy. The author put Joey in some situations where it would've been easier for him to run for cover than to follow his heart. This story reveals Ms. Dieckmann's keen imagination and creativity. It will be a joy to read the next book in this series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18336377689744168200" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

